The paper uses game theory to model deception in cyberspace, specifically in the context of network security. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of technology (such as detectors) to detect deception, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on analyzing interactions and designing mechanisms could also place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
